values: Pisces Horoscope for week of November 15, 2007 If you chew coca leaves, you get a mild buzz, comparable to coffee, because your body metabolizes only tiny amounts of the plant's alkaloids. But in cocaine, which is made from processed coca leaves, those same alkaloids are highly concentrated. Snorting or smoking the stuff gives your bloodstream a potent blast. Bolivia's president Evo Morales wants the world to know the difference between the two. "The coca leaf is not cocaine," he says. He pledges to completely legalize coca in his country, citing its traditional uses as a food and medicine predating the European invasion. Is there a comparable scenario in your life, Pisces? Something that's bad for you when done to excess, but good for you in its understated natural state? It's a favorable time to commit yourself to its healthy use.

I drive through my old neighborhood to get to work.

I go through a school zone. It's a predominately black and latin neighborhood. You may have remembered my rants about the garbage that is dropped in the streets everywhere. The city doesn't have people coming to clean up so it just sits there. While going through the school zone yesterday I see a white lady talking to the lone crossing guard. She is gesturing toward the garbage. I can tell what she is saying. She's complaining about the amount of trash around and how are the children supposed to feel about themselves if they have to look at this trash all the time. Maybe if a WHITE lady gets involved, someone will do something.

The day before I was driving down Holden and there was a bus stopped letting passengers on. There were 3 or 4 cars in front of me, and two behind. When the bus pulled away and traffic started moving, I noticed as I passed that there was a laptop case sitting on the bench. OMG! Someone left their computer on the bench? I couldn't stop, I couldn't turn around, I coudn't catch up with the bus. I felt useless.

I had the most unsetting thing happen to me last night. I was making my lunch for today, A chicken salad. I cooked (baked) the chicken in the oven, and was going to cut it into strips to put on the salad. I made three cause I have to get all the way to 10pm tonight.
I remember putting the chicken on the salad in the tupperware bowl. I got up this morning and the BOWLS WERE STILL SITTING ON THE COUNTER WITH THE TOPS OPEN! I couldn't believe it. What the hell was I thinking! I can't remember what happened between putting the chicken on the salad and going to sleep. It's blank. Not to mention all that food is wasted. I'm really freaked by this cause I have no idea what happened.

The roomies are so cool. They let me use their computer for the time being till I can get the hook up next week. They said that they had a music service and if I wanted to burn off some music to have @ it. I found some really rare cuts and made about 3 cds worth. (one being Luiz') I was jammin on the way to work this morning. I need to get some cool blank CDs. I want to get some of those that look like vinyl 45s. I also have to get some new headphones as the ones I have are so tired. I was thinking of getting one of those adaptorsfor the wireless headphones to plug in. So I can wild out without wires. I don't know what the sound quality is like tho.
_____________________________________

I feel I have been doing pretty well as far as sabotaging myself goes. It's not easy meeting people in general, and then ones that you are actually attracted to is even harder, so when it happens for me it's like rare like the northern lights or a comet falling or something. I don't want anything to mess it up. I have been practicing thinking positively about the situation. Visualizing the positive outcome I'd be comfortable with. I stood in questioning myself for a second. Do I mess things up by saying things like "This guy prolly isn't the love of my life, but he's cool enough to chill." I have a casual attitude about things, because I would like them to develop naturally. Not put things under pressure. I am open to things growing deeper, and more intense of course. I just have to get to know someone first. I don't think that is odd at all. However, there is a dynamic, that when a person starts to get attention from someone, and they like it. Whether or not they have a significant other becomes irrelevant. So they are eating it up with a girlfriend/ wife in the background. I HATE THAT! If someone flirts back with you, you can't just assume they are single. If they ask where you man is, that doesn't automatically mean they themselves are single. I HATE THAT THAT IS THE REALITY! The last "date" I went on was with a man who was still married. He claimed to be getting a divorce. But to me it seemed like he and the wife weren't getting along and he was just stepping out on her.

What I am getting @ is, I haven't verbally asked Luiz if he has a girlfriend, hell or a boyfriend! I gotta do it. I'm sitting here looking @ this CD I made him and it all came crashing down on my head. I have to ask him flat out. So I don't waste the energy. If I had a dollar for every time I wasted my energy on an unavailable man.. I wouldn't have a live journal cause I would be on full frolic with my possie in Europe someplace, living the millionaire lifestyle. No mas. Like Usher, gotta have it my way.

Ok, here's how it went down.

I went down to  the meat store a little before closing to pick up some chicken. Hair done, and make up fierce. I walk in, he is huddled up in a suede jacket, and khakis. It's cold in there.

We start talking about music again. He admits he hasn't heard my CD yet but it's in the car. He's rocking the new Jay Z, he says it's pretty good. We get on the subject of Prince and his crazy ways these days. He says he has the new Prince but didn't understand much of it. He said he'd make me a copy. I haven't heard great things about it however. But to have a CD he made for me. Wow. He sees my chicken, and asks if I am cooking tonight. I tell him yeah, when are you coming through? His eyebrows go up, like he's surprised I was so non chalaunt about it. He said he has something to do tonight. I made the cute pouty face, and said I'd try my best not to be hurt. He puts his hand over his heart and says "That's the last thing I want to do to you is hurt you." I was like, no it's cool, it's pretty short notice. I should respect you more, and give you some notice. I'd want the same courtesy. I was just trying to get my feet wet anyway by asking. If he would have said yeah, the game would have changed. He says he doesn't even know where I live. I tell him the area, and what the route is quickest. He understood. I couldn't help but wonder what he had to do, but I'll keep my musings to myself. We talked and talked till customers came in, again, and I excused myself and told him to listen to the CD. He said ok, the end.

WHAT UP WITH THESE GAS PRICES YO~!

Ok this is what happened.

I went to the meat store at 4:40pm as planned. I usually buy a bag of puffy cheetos as a cover. But they were out. So I asked Luiz if they had more. He said they get a shipment on Friday. There are a steady stream of customers coming to the counter and he is ringing them up. His uncle is at the counter across the aisle, so I am feeling very self consious about the whole "saying how I feel thing." I brought a mix CD with me with Roots, Tribe, Alicia and Prince on it for him to rock. I told him my favorite group was the Roots once when we were talking, and he didn't really know alot of their music. SO I gave him the CD and told him I'd be back Saturday. 

I'll show up about closing time, and see what I can get jumpin.

Dayumm he's fyne.

TO me anyway.

Oriental Silk with denim back. white sequin cotton tube top and denim skirt. I was in a long skirt phase for a while. Naturally that was before I moved to a hot climate. Those got chopped right off! I'll keep looking for more photos. _______________________________________________ I was finishing packing the apartment up on Saturday night and Jeb shows up, and asks if he can come in. I say sure since it is his place. He is just blabbing on and on. Talking about how he was going to go to the convention center to work, like banquet set up for money. Then he bailed because "It wasn't him." I looked at him blank and kept packing. He is the LAZIEST PERSON ALIVE! He has this notion that he doesn't have to work, and people should just pay him for breathing. Not literally, but he's got two properties and no job. He makes tons of excuses for not working and he doesn't have much of an imagination when it comes to finding a job, or the willingness to submit for the greater good. He has hidden out with low life for so long, that he can't look a man in a suit in the eye without feeling like a lump of garbage. At one point he says "Live and learn." I couldn't help but to chime in "Let's hope someday you will and change some shit." He stopped, "What does that mean." "Just what I said. You want the new stuff with the old behavior, and it doesn't work that way." He had no clue what I was saying, which is typical. It felt good to walk away. It really did. Forward, never back.

I moved a load of stuff to the new house last night. The place is really cute. My room is small but workable with the right shelving units. Definately going to be that winter cave for sure. It's so great to be leaving that God forsaken neighborhood. I was driving to work this morning and saw big bags of garbage in the road again. <font size=7>I MEAN WHO THE FUCK DOES THAT!!!</font> It's disgusting. More disturbing is that it isn't removed and you can drive by it for days at a time, and that no one is fined for it. It's like if you see an accident, a crew comes after and cleans up all the glass and debris. Not in the hood, you will be driving through glass for the rest of the year. It will be nice to be out of there, away from Jeb-and on to the next chapter of life. I am beaming with excitement!

The roomies are all youngins, employed and cool. Finally a decent living situation. But the whole house meeting thing will be inevitable, dishes are always the thing that can set a war in motion in shared living situations. The youngest one works two jobs too. I guess I am automatically house mom being the oldest. But I'm one of those fair moms, that tells you what the expectation is, and then lets you take care of it. I don't want to nag people to be clean. Just encourage and explain why it's important to be a clean person, yanno?

I went to look @ the room on Saturday. It was in a decent neighborhood, over the river and through the woods from where I live now. FINALLY I will be out of the hood!

The women there already are cool, laid back types. The room is the same size as the one I have now. Though I have my own apartment now, all I use is the bedroom. I have a living area, with nothing in it. A rug, that's it. I signed the lease and can start moving my stuff in whenever. I will have HIGH SPEED INTERNET FINALLY! WOO HOO! I can LJ from home finally! And chat! I can't so much at work, the boss lady frowns upon it. So that's taken care of. Mr Nice guy voulenteered his time and self to help me move. He's the sweetest. He could have anything he wanted if he'd just ask.

I'll start packing and putting stuff in boxes tonight. And packing my trunk with clothes and shoes. 

SO EXCITED~!

I had this weird dream that there was a club (the dancing kind) in my bathroom. There is an alcove b/t my room and the actual bathroom. I have satin drapes that seperate the areas. I dreamed people would open the bathroom door when they were leaving and I would hear loud music, they would be drunk and trying to be quiet but I could hear their footsepts and it would disturb me. I was saying "get out, be quiet" in my sleep. 

I realized my landlord came into my house when I wasn't there after the fight. He got his laundry soap as he left it there the other day cause his washer broke. And his mail, cause people still send it to my mailbox. It annoyed me he was in my house after I wrote his loser ass off.

It seems to be an epidemic, insecure men. Men who are totally posessive and moving way to fast in relationships. It's that internet mentality, instant relationship, instant marriage, instant sex. No one wants to work to get anything anymore, and that's what's wrong with Americans in general, we are spoiled and think we are entitiled to everything we see. Hell, Mexicans could be the best thing to ever happen to us and we can't even admit it because we are so bigotted and short sided. At least they are willing to put in a hard days work. I aint mad at them. 

The bosses are gone today so everyone is slacking big time. Hey it's Friday. The kids are out of school today too for whatever reason so all the roads are deserted. I went to lunch at 12 and there was no line! It was AWESOME! I was the only one in there. 

My friend Chad and I have been texting the past two days. He is one guy that can find him some woman drama! WHOOOOO! It's craaaaaazy. But it seems like he finally found a good one. He's a good guy. 

Is it me or does it seem like there are more reality shows than actual ones on TV now.

Have to go and meet the peeps at the house in the AM, I hope they are cool. She had hip hop on her phone message which is a good sign. If it were speed metal I would have hung up, and crossed their name off the list. 

Wish me luck!

Did anyone catch the 6 hour special in VH1 Classic last night? OMG! What I caught was amazing. They went from Delta blues all the way to present day. The last hour they did a huge segment on Mary J Blige. The Hour before that they did Aretha Franklin. I wished I saw it from the beginning because it was so well crafted. I guess it's a british creation. AWESOME! http://www.bbc.co.uk/music/souldeep/

And so this whole blow up wasn't actually a bad thing. I have been feeling overwhelmed and stuck. I work my ass off 13 hours a day just to pay bills. I am not paying off my student loan so I can go to school next fall. NOT anywhere near it. So it motivated me to cut all ties and move into a shared house for half the money and no extra bills. The money that I save I can use to start paying toward the future.

I put on my fight club shirt to wear to work today and I started thinking about the movie. How Ed Norton created Tyler Durden to get him out of his rut, to give him free. I need a little Tyler to help me get free to, just not blow stuff up. But it's an amazing concept. Maybe I'll watch it again tonight.

I'm always in a good mood on Wednesday cause it's my official day off from the night job. Not that lately I have been there much. I have decided to move out of my complex completely. You see there was a serious arguement between Jeb and I night before last and I am so done with him it's not even funny. He's my landlord. But he was my friend first. Jeb has this personality where he seeks out people who are worse off than him and befriends them so he has the upper hand so to speak. Even his last girlfriend moved into his place so then he could pull rank on her that way too. He came to me and asked if I would rent his place cause "He didn't trust anyone else to live there." Cause basically everyone else he knows is a loser. Druggie drunk or con artist. I hesitated because I know how he is, go it on my own. He kept telling me "I'll only charge you $400 cause that's what the mortgage is on the place." You can't beat that rent for a one bedroom anywhere remotely urban. So I considered it. I told him I was considering it, then he says "I actually will need $500." Still less than anywhere else I could move into. Then it was $550. The places I found in the area for one beds were $575 to $675. He kept asking me, and sounded more and more desprate. So I said how about I pay you $600 and pay you twice a month. He agreed. But of course when I moved in he didn't remember the conversation but wanted $600 in one lump sum. Did I mention he wasn't going to charge me a deposit either, then waited till the last minute to say he needed one too? $150. But I didn't have to pay that right away. I gave him $400 and a few days later the other $200 and then two weeks after that $150. For the entire 16 months I have lived there that has pretty much been how we do it. $400 on the 5th and $200 a week later. I have OFFERED to pay late fees. "No no no that's ok." Then on the phone the other night "I have been more than lenient with you and haven't charged you any late fees." So let me get this straight. Because you MADE THE CHOICE not to charge late fees then that's my fault somehow. He kept saying it, and I told him "Do me a personal favor. As a friend, please do not talk about how nice you have been about not charging me late fees. I just can't take it right now." Then he gets loud. "Well I have!" I told him "Let's do it this way you give me a bill for all the late fees, and then stop bringing it up." "That would be thousands of dollars!!!!" he screams. I grab my calculator "Well let's see, I have lived here 16 months, x $35 a months comes out to $560. NOT THOUSANDS OF DOLLARS!!!" He got even more pissed. "SO GIVE ME A BILL AND STOP BRINGING IT UP! I DONT WANT TO HEAR IT!" I told him "You know who does things for you and expects some sort of loyalty or payment after? A PIMP! You have a pimp mentality. You don't have friends, you hire dependents. Everyone has to have a debt to you so you can prove 'what a nice guy you are' and nice guys DONT CONSTANTLY POINT IT OUT AND BRING IT UP!" Needless to say he kept cutting me off when I was talking, and yelling over me. "This exact thing is why you don't have any friends now!" I said and hung up. He calls back, I don't answer. He comes up the stairs but doesn't knock. He has been hiding since. Good. I hate his ass..... cont. gotta go back to the grind...

I love the weekend. It didn't rain for a change. I cleaned the house saturday as I always do, did my hair. I hate it. It's way to short. Got dressed and thought I would do errands before I met up with my cuz for the movies at 3:00. Went by the meat store, and it felt like a month or two since I had been there. There was a guy standing at the station talking to Luiz, and I thought by the time I was done shopping he'd be gone and I could talk to Luiz. I do so look forward to our little chats. But NOOOOOOOOOO dood was still standing there! I was so mad. Luiz was like "I detect some negativity coming from you." I was mad tired so I just said that was what it was, but I wanted to tell dood to bounce. I told Luiz I'd be back the next day. My cuz and I went to see Why did I get married. It was OFF THE CHAIN! Great film. They didn't miss a beat. Great cast. Funny, and sad too. After the movie we went for cheap Mexican, and talked for like two hours. I don't see my cuz hardly enough. The next day I went back to the meat store and it was empty. I got my meat and went to the counter. I loaned him my Stevie4real CD, the one with all the Timbaland mixes on it. He was excited to listen to it. Then we talked music, becuase I know he's an addict like I am for the beats. He told me he plays classical and jazz trumpet. I was impressed. He asked what my favorite groups are. "Who is your absolute favorite hip hop artist?" I told him the ROOTS. They are the top of my list. He was like cool, tho I don't think he really knows who they are. We talked about travelling, and he said he'd like to travel alot. Then....this woman came in saying "Hi honey!" She was older and had a nametag on like she was a waitress or something. Spanish speaking. I looked for his reaction, like is that hi honey like that's your woman, or is that just a customer that's friendly. I couldn't get a reading, so I exused myself; because if she came to the counter and started a conversation in the middle of my conversation and in SPANISH I would have snapped for real. So I told him I'd see him later. (grumble) My landlord keeps jerking me back and forth. I didn't have to move at all, then I have to move in 2 weeks, then not till November 29th. He told me Thursday October 27th. Then I could keep the last three days of the months rent since I'll be living in another apartment then. Cool $60 I can pay bills with. Friday was payday. He calls to see if I am going to meet him as ususal to give him the remaider of the rent for this month. I say yes. He says he's a little busy so he may come by my work, which he has done before. Cool. I go cash my check and pay some bills. Then when I get home he's asking for the $60 cause he's changed his mind again! I was LIVID! I told him he would have to wait because I already used the money. And besides you told me one thing yesterday, why didn't you tell me this on the phone when you spoke to me this morning? Cause he changed his mind since that morning! HE GETS ON MY NERVES! I was listening to the lyrics of "That Thing" by Lauren Hill, and it's so ironic because she didn't listen to her own advice!

I came in this morning to a note back from my friend abroad. Your forgiveness is exceedingly kind and massively appreciated. My computer linked onto everyone in my address book and contacted everyone in it. Thanks for your understanding and kindness. T To which I wrote: I think you know, what you mean to me and what you have given me will always outweigh any disapointment I may have. Love you no matter. L I love brilliant men, I can't help it. It's a relief that that wasn't going to be a big production. I guess he thought that I was so hurt by him not being able to see me his last visit. I was, but I got over it. You do that when stuff matters to you. I know he's busy when he's here. If he can fit me in that's cool. If not, I understand. I'm disapointed, but I understand. So that's a load off.

I have had girlfriends who meet men and in a short time become engaged. 

Several of them have found themselves knee deep in disaster, lies, deceit and pregnancies by men that they really didn't know. Then stuck like chuck.

One girlfriend who had come from "the life" got clean and sober, quit stripping, went to school for interior design, and then got a great paying job in the field. She got a house in the nicest neighborhood in town; which had always been a dream of hers. She went to church, and slowly over time became quite legalistic about hers. She met a man in church that "was meant for her". It didn't hurt that he was tall sexy and Italian, and in real estate either. She kept this relationship from me for 4 months and the fifth month they were getting married. She had gotten pregnant by the man, and when she told him, he disappeared. She would then find out that he had been cheating on her the whole time they were together. And that his real estate career was on line, and not that lucrative. She had two teenage boys that were quite rebellious, so she shipped them to military school. The Italian came back, and they got married. She quit her job, and lives in his fixer uppers with him. When I finally met the guy, he gave me the willies; but it's her life not mine.

Now I have another friend engaged to a guy she's known three months. He works at her gym and is quite sexy, and also claims to be in real estate tho the market is slow. I smell trouble.

Some say, seize the day, go for it. 

Some say take your time, and get to know the man a while. 

What do yall thank?

She was all of 80 pounds and look like she hadn't eaten for months. When some of the men got "saved" they wanted to get on the mike and sing too. I wasn't going to stay till 9pm. I made my weekly meat store appearance. Luis was the only one there. I went pretty late. They keep the store pretty cool because of all the meat. Luiz just had on a t shirt and jeans. He was having a hard time communiacting with a Hatian woman about pork shoulders. Her english was terrible. I got my groceries and went to the counter. Luiz asks for my hand. I give it to him, he holds it a moment and says "You're warm. Warm hands, warm heart." I guess that's true. Just him touching my hand and looking in my eyes was a moment in time. It's like he isn't sure if I like him or not. Which is so cute to me. When he gives me my change sometimes he does it slowly and makes sure our fingers touch. So utterly Victorian. Sneaking a touch. I printed out the info on the rainbow for him and had it in my purse. I took it out all folded up and handed it to him. He looks at the folded paper, and asks if he can read it now or should he wait till later. Cute, he thinks it's a love letter. "You can read it now." So he unfolds it and sees it's about the rainbow. "Ohhhh you remembered." He laughed. "Yeah, I told you I would print you something. I'm a woman of my word." He looks up from the paper. "You say what I mean." he said. "That's right." I said "You are who you say you are." he added. He was saying something more than his words indicated. I'm @ the point where I am just curious if he will ever say anything. Or if he won't because he's working and doesn't want to cross any lines. It's got all this nervous energy around it. It's nice. Keeps the blood pumping.
